the review just underneath me, by a &#34;Jason&#34; is accurate:

&#34;Better than the one at the streets. Nicer staff and bigger portions. Don&#39;t know why it has such a low rating. Keep up the good work chipotle team.&#34;  

Amen.

Tried this place twice in one week!!!.  Amazing pav bhaji, not sure what that white stuff is in a cup, looks like it&#39;s suppose to be onion but mixed with lettuce!  HAHAHA desi style to increase quantity, adding some cheap lettuce.   I agree with other Yelpers quantity is not sufficient; Something really weird is going on with their quantity; 

I had Dhosa and didn&#39;t think sambhar / daal was sufficient for me to finish dhosa.  I&#39;ve also tried their pani puri which isn&#39;t what you would remember from Ahmedabad.  

Looks like Honest name with some &#39;faltu&#39; recipe!

I came here with a friend on New Year Day. It was empty which worried me. We sat down, ordered a bunch of food. It was ALLL delicious. We kinda slept in too late and missed brunch but lunch was good. 

// Popcorn shrimp tempura - 14 - This was so tasty and light. The popcorn shrimp was spot on. 

// Crispy brussels sprouts and kale - 14 - THIS IS A MUST. so delicious, they mix it for you at the table and has this delicious dressing on it. 

// malaysian pork and shrimp fried eggs - 14 -  I enjoyed this because there was a fried egg on top. It was yolky and messy. Definitely worth trying. 

// Bloody mary - strong, bloody, tasty. 

I am glad this place is in the suburbs.. now I finally have an option for good food. they also have sushi here, which i was unable to try but it sounds delicious. It is a little pricey, my friend and I ended up paying 90$ with drinks. Kinda steep for two people but tasty! Definitely coming back here!
